The paper discusses the implementation of agile software development principles in companies that develop software-intense mechatronic systems. This involves the integration of software, hardware, and mechanics, which falls under the categories of software engineering (cs.SE), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), embedded systems (cs.EM), and software development (cs.SD). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
